UN Says Gbagbo Army Chiefs Will Order Ivory Coast Troops to Stop Fighting

-- B y   P a u l i n e   B a x
-- 
2011-04-05T12:47:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/un-says-gbagbo-army-chiefs-will-order-ivory-coast-troops-to-stop-fighting.html
Phillippe Mangou, the chief of staff
of the army of Ivory Coast’s President  Laurent Gbagbo , and Bruno
Dogbo Ble, the head of his Republican Guard, told the  United
Nations  that they will stop fighting and asked for protection,
Hamadoun Toure, a spokesman for the UN, said in an interview
from Abidjan today.  The military leaders said they would hand over their arms
to the UN, he said.  Gbagbo’s troops have been fighting rebels loyal to Alassane
Ouattara.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pauline Bax in Johannesburg at 
 pbax@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
